Etymology[edit]

From pāx (“peace”).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈpaː.koː/
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈpa.ko/, [ˈpaː.kɔ]

Verb[edit]

pācō (present infinitive pācāre, perfect active pācāvī, supine pācātum); first conjugation

  1. I make peaceful, pacify, quiet, soothe; subdue
    Synonym: pācificō
  2. (Late or Medieval Latin) I settle, satisfy
